 SA Hip Hop was a genre that was ridiculed by other artists and members of the public about a decade ago because it wasn’t making as much money as it does today. The genre has since grown to be the most prominent and most lucrative genre in South Africa. A lot of rappers have been cashing in big guap so we decided to compile a list of Hip Hops top earners: 1. Die Entwoord The South African rap-rave group has been making money off their music for a while now. The group has been releasing music since 09 which has enabled them to headline a lot of international tours in Europe and on different parts of the world. The group is said to have a networth of R56 million  and a yearly revenue of 8 Million.     Cassper Nyovest relocating to America Cassper Nyovest closes in on Minnie Dlamini I needed to grow up that's why i removed the ponytail - Cassper Nyovest These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content  Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More